âœ… Instance Variable in Java

An instance variable is a variable that is:

ğŸ‘‰ Declared inside a class

ğŸ‘‰ But outside any method

ğŸ‘‰ Each object (instance) of the class gets its own copy

ğŸ“Œ Simple Example:
class Student {
    int age;   // instance variable

    void show() {
        System.out.println(age);
    }
}


Explanation:

age is an instance variable

Every Student object will have its own age

ğŸ“Œ Usage Example:
Student s1 = new Student();
Student s2 = new Student();

s1.age = 20;
s2.age = 22;

System.out.println(s1.age); // 20
System.out.println(s2.age); // 22

ğŸ‘‰ Each object stores a different value.

