ğŸ“¦ What is an Array?

ğŸ‘‰ An array is a collection of same type of values
ğŸ‘‰ Stored in continuous memory locations
ğŸ‘‰ Accessed using index (position)

<type>[] <object-name> = new type[size];

---

Write a Java program to find the sum of even and odd numbers in a given range.
import java.util.Scanner;

class Range{
    public static void main(String[] a){
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("Enter Starting range: ");
        int start=sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println("Enter ending range: ");
        int end=sc.nextInt();
        int oddsum=0;
        int evensum=0;
        for(int i=start;i<=end;i++){
            if(i%2==0){
                evensum=evensum+i;
            }
            else if(i%2!=0){
                oddsum=oddsum+i;
            }
        }
        System.out.println("Sum of even number: " + evensum);
        System.out.println("Sum of odd number: " + oddsum);
    }
}

